<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-09-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lardy</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Manchester, Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-09-15"><hi rend="italic">September 15, 1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President of the Swiss Confederation, after wiring to Mrs. McKinley
                            and calling personally on Mr. Hardy, has sent me the following message:
                                <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The Federal Council, deeply moved by the demise of President
                                    McKinley, who succumbed to the effects of a heinous attempt,
                                    directs that you expressly convey its sympathy to the Government
                                    of the Union and to the family of the deceased. The entire Swiss
                                    people share these sentiments.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lardy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires of Switzerland</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>